Piece Wise Grapher App made by Jay-lab27
Functions Supported in Piecewise Expressions ✅
Input Parsing Support:
Your app handles these algebraic functions:

Linear: x, 2x, x+1, x-4, 3x+2
Quadratic: x², x^2, 2x², etc.
Absolute Value: |x|, |x-1|, |2x|, etc.
Square Root: √x, sqrt(x)
Rational: x/2, 1/x, etc.
Polynomial: combinations with +, -, *, /, ^ operators
Graphing Evaluation Support:
When graphing, the app evaluates:

✅ abs() - absolute value
✅ sin() - sine (in radians)
✅ cos() - cosine (in radians)
✅ tan() - tangent (in radians)
✅ log() - natural logarithm
✅ ln() - natural logarithm
✅ exp() - exponential function
✅ sqrt() - square root
✅ floor() - floor function
✅ ceil() / ceiling() - ceiling function
✅ sgn() / sign() - signum (sign function)
✅ round() - rounding function
Mathematical Operators Supported:
Addition: +
Subtraction: -
Multiplication: * (also implicit like 2x)
Division: /
Exponentiation: ^ or **
Domain Condition Support:
x < a (less than)
x ≤ a (less than or equal)
x > a (greater than)
x ≥ a (greater than or equal)
Compound: -3 ≤ x < -1
